         MACRO                                                          00160000
.*                                                                      00170000
.* Branch and Link on condition                                         00180000
.*                                                                      00190000
&LABEL   BALC  &COND,                  * Condition                     *00200000
               &REG,                   * Register for return address   *00210000
               &DEST,                  * Destination address or (reg)  *00220000
               &TYPE=LOCAL             * BAL/BALR                       00230000
.*                                                                      00240000
.* &COND specifies on which condition the BAL is to be executed         00250000
.*       valid values are:  E,  H,  L,  M,  O,  P,  Z, and              00260000
.*                         NE, NH, NL, NM, NO, NP, NZ                   00270000
.* &REG  Specifies the register to contain the return address           00280000
.* &DEST Specifies the address to branch to. If specified as a          00290000
.*       (register) a BALR will be generated in stead of a BAL.         00300000
.* &TYPE Specifies whether the designated routine is reached thru       00310000
.*       a local (BAL) branch or a remote (BALR) branch                 00320000
.*                                                                      00321001
.********************************************************************** 00324001
.*                                                                      00325001
.*       IMPORTANT NOTICE                                               00326001
.*       ========= ======                                               00327001
.*                                                                      00328001
